entries.title: Elon Musk Testifies That His Tweets Did Not Drive Tesla’s Stock Price
entries.description: The chief executive of Tesla testified in a federal civil trial about a 2018 plan to take the automaker private that fizzled out.

entries.title: Tech Layoffs Shock Young Workers. The Older People? Not So Much.
entries.description: The industry’s recent job cuts have been an awakening for a generation of workers who have never experienced a cyclical crash.

entries.title: Elon’s Crumbling Empire and Generative A.I. Goes to Court
entries.description: And, a cautionary tale for the media using A.I.

entries.title: Meta’s Oversight Board Calls for Overhaul of Nude Photo Standards
entries.description: A dispute over photos of bare chests with the nipples covered, posted on Instagram by a transgender and nonbinary couple, has prompted a call for the platform to clarify its content guidelines.

entries.title: The Chatbots Can’t Outsmart You. Yet.
entries.description: The Turing test used to be the gold standard for proving machine intelligence. This generation of bots is racing past it. We need to stay calm — and develop a new test.

entries.title: Google Calls in Help From Larry Page and Sergey Brin for A.I. Fight
entries.description: A rival chatbot has shaken Google out of its routine, with the founders who left three years ago re-engaging and more than 20 A.I. projects in the works.

entries.title: Genesis, a Crypto Lending Firm, Files for Bankruptcy
entries.description: Genesis was caught in the fallout of the collapse of FTX, the crypto exchange founded by Sam Bankman-Fried.

entries.title: T-Mobile Says Hacker Got Data From 37 Million Customer Accounts
entries.description: The breach exposed information like names, addresses and phone numbers and lasted more than a month, the company reported in a securities filing.
